  "texts": [
    "The inference is thus that while food delivery locations are everywhere, the nutritional quality of meals is poor, mainly due to structural factors that limit consumers from acting in line with dietary intentions.",
    "This study aims to investigate the food habits and preferences among young adults in the context of food delivery.",
    "Based on the discussions, the following conclusions are drawn: 72.45% of the respondents chose convenience over nutrition when buying food online, though 61.23% said they did consider nutritional value.",
    "Yet only 30.62% followed healthier meals over the duration.",
    "This difference indicates that convenience always comes first in real life."
  ],
